{"title":"Specialized creates custom S-Works Tarmac SL7s for its two road world champions","link":"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/pro-bike/custom-specialized-tarmac-sl7-world-champions/","date":1619178024000,"content":"<img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9052-b75ca42.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=620,413\" />                                            <p><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/brand/specialized/\">Specialized</a> has created two custom S-Works Tarmac SL7 road bikes for the two current UCI road world champions, Anna van der Breggen and Julian Alaphilippe, ahead of this weekend’s Liège-Bastogne-Liège.</p>\n<p>Decked out with a white and rainbow stripe paint job, and designed by Elena Aker (a concept bike designer for Specialized), each SL7 is inspired by the iconic world champions’ jersey, and blessed with a series of individual flourishes intended to celebrate the two riders.</p>\n<p>There’s no new tech here – underneath that paint it’s the same <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/bikes/road-bikes/specialized-s-works-tarmac-sl7-review/\">Venge-killing, aero-yet-lightweight race bike we reviewed last summer</a> (a bike Specialized says is the “the winningest bike of 2021 so far”) – but it’s always worth pausing to appreciate beautiful custom paint jobs when you get the opportunity.</p>\n<div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9474-ecfbef1.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Anna van der Breggen’s custom-painted Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9160-076c982.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>SD Worx’s mechanics set about building the frameset up from scratch.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9244-547d44c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The early part of the build involves sorting out all of the internal routing for the hydraulic brake hoses.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9297-1b45504.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Van der Breggen is a two-time world champion, so this isn’t her first rainbow-themed bike.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9521-31bbc87.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Van der Breggen’s bike has a SRAM Red eTap AXS groupset.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9306-ed94cc4.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The wheels are Zipp 202 disc wheels, shod with Specialized Turbo Cotton ‘Hell of the North’ 28mm tubular tyres.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9516-7c46a10.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The rainbow stripes mirror the iconic jersey worn awarded to UCI world champions.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9375-0f1440b.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Even the pros love new bike day.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/AVDB_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC9384-746795e.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Van der Breggen taking her custom Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7 for a test spin ahead of Sunday’s final Ardennes classic, Liège–Bastogne–Liège.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>Riding for Team SD Worx, van der Breggen’s bike is decked out with a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/groupsets/groupset-road/sram-12-speed-red-etap-axs-hrd-review/\">SRAM Red eTap AXS groupset</a>, <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/wheels/wheel-sets/zipp-202-nsw-disc-review/\">Zipp 202 disc wheels</a> shod with <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/tyres/specialized-turbo-cotton-hell-of-the-north-first-ride-review/\">Specialized Turbo Cotton ‘Hell of the North’ 28mm tubular tyres</a>, a Zipp handlebar and stem, Time pedals and a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/saddles/specialized-s-works-power-with-mirror-saddle-review/\">Specialized S-Works Power with Mirror saddle</a>.</p>\n<p>Being one of the most decorated riders in the peloton (van der Breggen won La Flèche Wallonne for a seventh consecutive time on Wednesday), this is actually the second time Specialized has created a world champion-themed bike for the Dutch rider. The first came in December 2018, when Specialized created a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/pro-bike/colour-explosion-for-van-der-breggens-world-champion-tarmac-sl6-disc/\">custom S-Works Tarmac SL6</a> for the recently-crowned world champion.</p>\n<div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8632-da1cba7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Julian Alaphilippe’s custom-painted Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8323-376d440.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>A Deceuninck-QuickStep begins the build for Alaphilippe’s custom Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8365-bfd897a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Alaphilippe’s position on the bike is painstakingly replicated using precise fit measurements.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8483-efe7531.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The frameset is adorned with small details inspired by Alaphilippe and his team.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8636-f8eea56.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>More details on the down tube.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8694-209cace.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Alaphilippe’s bike has a Shimano Dura-Ace R9170 Di2 groupset.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8700-a6d69cb.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Alaphilippe chooses PRO handlebars.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8709-021e363.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Deceuninck-QuickStep are currently racing on Roval Rapide CLX wheels with Specialized Turbo Cotton clincher tyres.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8718-6323658.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Specialized’s latest Tarmac is said to be so fast it made the Venge obsolete.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8737-a1a6dd8.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Alaphilippe receiving his custom-painted Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8752-099f92b.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>He seems to like it…</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/04/JA_Rainbow-Specialized-Tarmac-SL7_ETSC8886-0c60752.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Alaphilippe will attempt to win Liège–Bastogne–Liège for the first time on Sunday.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Specialized</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>Alaphilippe’s bike is built up with a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/groupsets/groupset-road/shimano-dura-ace-di2-r9170-first-ride-review/\">Shimano Dura-Ace R9170 Di2</a> groupset and pedals, with a PRO handlebar, a Specialized S-Works Romin Evo saddle and a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/roval-rapide-alpinist-clx-wheelset/\">Roval Rapide CLX wheelset</a> shod with <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/tyres/specialized-s-works-turbo-cotton-tire-review/\">Specialized Turbo Cotton clincher tyres</a> (yep, that’s correct – <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/pro-bike/2021-tour-of-flanders-clinchers/\">Deceuninck-QuickStep riders are using and winning on clinchers</a> at the moment). The valve stems also appear to be those of Vittoria latex <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/bike-inner-tubes/\">inner tubes</a>.</p>\n<p>This is Alaphilippe’s first season in the rainbow stripes, but the ‘<a href=\"https://www.bmj.com/content/351/bmj.h6304\" target=\"_blank\">curse of the rainbow jersey</a>’ appears not to have held him back so far, with the Frenchman finishing second at Strade Bianche, winning a stage of Tirreno-Adriatico and winning La Flèche Wallonne on Wednesday.</p>\n<p>Both van der Breggen and Alaphilippe will race their new bikes for the first time at <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/search/?q=Li%C3%A8ge-Bastogne-Li%C3%A8ge\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège</a>, on Sunday, before continuing to use them throughout the rest of the 2021 season.</p>\n<p><em>What do you think of the two custom bikes? Would you ride a bike with a rainbow paint job, or should they be reserved for world champions only? Let us know in the comments below.</em></p>","author":"Simon Bromley","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"9e54fb75a06901c4eee92562bce6ca84ccdab1cefdae88bbad8fe865b9b4964b","category":"Cycling"}